-- Australia, N.Z., South Africa Tune Up for Tri-Nations Rugby With Victories
-- Dan Baynes
-- 2010-06-26T16:06:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-26/australia-n-z-south-africa-tune-up-for-tri-nations-rugby-with-victories.html

          
          
             New Zealand, Australia and South
Africa all tuned up for the Tri-Nations rugby series with home
victories over northern hemisphere teams.  
 The All Blacks extended their winning run over Wales to 23
matches with a 29-10 victory in the second Test in Hamilton,
while the Wallabies kept Ireland try-less in a 22-15 win in
their one-off Test in Brisbane.  
 Morne Steyn scored 26 points and Bryan Habana tied the
South African try-scoring record as the world champion
Springboks beat Italy 55-11 in East London to seal a 2-0 series
victory. Habana touched down once to take his tally to 38 in 60
Tests, equaling Joost van der Westhuizenâ€™s tally in 89 matches.  
 New Zealand hosts defending champion South Africa in the
opening Tri-Nations matches on July 10 and 17.  
          
          


  


        